title: An Argument Against Drug Testing Welfare Recipients

affiliations.name: Mary Jean Walker, PhD, has research interests in bioethics, personal and narrative identity, and health policy. She has worked on ethical and epistemic issues related to advanced medical devices, overdiagnosis, the epistemology of surgery, regulation of therapeutic goods, responsible research and innovation, and drug policy. Her doctorate examined psychological continuity and narrative theories of personal identity.
